<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-14155] xpath throws NPE if body is null when saxon is used as JAXP implementation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-14155</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;despite &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/javax/xml/xpath/XPathExpression.html#evaluate-java.lang.Object-javax.xml.namespace.QName-&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;XPath API spec&lt;/a&gt; states:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;If a null value is provided for item, an empty document will be used for the context&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;saxon, starting from 9.6, they decided to ignore it and throw NPE if the node is null, from &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.saxonica.com/html/documentation9.8/javadoc/net/sf/saxon/xpath/XPathExpressionImpl.html#evaluate-java.lang.Object-javax.xml.namespace.QName-&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;saxon javadoc&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Contrary to the interface specification, Saxon does not supply an empty document when the value is null. This is because XPath 2.0 allows the context item to be &quot;absent&quot; (null). So Saxon executes the XPath expression with the context item undefined.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;So in case of xpath expression is executed against a null body or header, saxon throws an NPE&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
